"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771387","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-24","<p>The government continues to support the development of a public country-by-country reporting model that operates on a multilateral basis as this would help ensure effective implementation.</p><p> </p><p>The Chancellor of the Exchequer and other Treasury Ministers continue to meet with their European counterparts on a regular basis, including at the Economic and Financial Affairs (ECOFIN) Council, to discuss issues including tax transparency.</p><p> </p><p>The UK will continue to engage constructively with the European Commission proposal for public country-by-country reporting.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","107886","2017-10-24T09:28:43.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771387/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771387/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771387/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-16","Multinational Companies: Company Accounts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to support public country by country reporting.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","107885"
